replies.bodyText:
Yes agreed!
It seems logical to define the scope of an operation within the context of a filter. After* operators seem to extend that scope after everything else outside that scope. Drawing an analogy to an imperative programming model:
public Result someMethod(Caller caller) {

    State state;
    try {
        state = new State();
        Result result = doWork();
        return result;
    } finally {
         // Code here is analogous to beforeFinally async operators.
         state.cleanup(); 
        // In order to demonstrate cleanup from the code that is calling this method. 
        // Assume caller is passed to this method.
        caller.cleanup();
    }
// Code below this is analogous to async afterFinally operators.
}

